{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:proverbs.18",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 18,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 18 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:1",
      "text": "A man who isolates himself pursues selfishness, and defies all sound judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:2",
      "text": "A fool has no delight in understanding, but only in revealing his own opinion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:3",
      "text": "When wickedness comes, contempt also comes, and with shame comes disgrace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:4",
      "text": "The words of a man’s mouth are like deep waters. The fountain of wisdom is like a flowing brook.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:5",
      "text": "To be partial to the faces of the wicked is not good, nor to deprive the innocent of justice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:6",
      "text": "A fool’s lips come into strife, and his mouth invites beatings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:7",
      "text": "A fool’s mouth is his destruction, and his lips are a snare to his soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:8",
      "text": "The words of a gossip are like dainty morsels: they go down into a person’s innermost parts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:9",
      "text": "One who is slack in his work is brother to him who is a master of destruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:10",
      "text": "Yahweh’s name is a strong tower: the righteous run to him, and are safe.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:11",
      "text": "The rich man’s wealth is his strong city, like an unscalable wall in his own imagination.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:12",
      "text": "Before destruction the heart of man is proud, but before honor is humility.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:13",
      "text": "He who answers before he hears, that is folly and shame to him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:14",
      "text": "A man’s spirit will sustain him in sickness, but a crushed spirit, who can bear?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:15",
      "text": "The heart of the discerning gets knowledge. The ear of the wise seeks knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:16",
      "text": "A man’s gift makes room for him, and brings him before great men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:17",
      "text": "He who pleads his cause first seems right — until another comes and questions him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:18",
      "text": "The lot settles disputes, and keeps strong ones apart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:19",
      "text": "A brother offended is more difficult than a fortified city. Disputes are like the bars of a fortress.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:20",
      "text": "A man’s stomach is filled with the fruit of his mouth. With the harvest of his lips he is satisfied.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:21",
      "text": "Death and life are in the power of the tongue; those who love it will eat its fruit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:22",
      "text": "Whoever finds a wife finds a good thing, and obtains favor of Yahweh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:23",
      "text": "The poor plead for mercy, but the rich answer harshly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.18.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 18:24",
      "text": "A man of many companions may be ruined, but there is a friend who sticks closer than a brother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
